// Throttle hits (HTTP 429) per developer over the last 24h, broken down by WHICH
// throttle fired.
//
// WHY GATEWAY LOGS (not customMetrics): the inbound `copilot_byok_request` metric is
// emitted BEFORE the three throttle policies run, so a rejected call still counts as a
// request and customMetrics cannot see the 429. The gateway log, by contrast, records
// the final ResponseCode AND the policy that produced it (LastErrorSource), so it is the
// only place a throttle rejection is visible per developer.
//
// The three throttles all return 429; LastErrorSource tells them apart:
//   rate-limit-by-key         -> burst (calls/min) exceeded
//   azure-openai-token-limit  -> TPM (tokens/min) cost guard exceeded  <- the AI-cost limit
//   quota-by-key              -> monthly call ceiling exceeded
//
// DEVELOPER IDENTITY: in subscriptionKey mode (default) the per-developer key is the APIM
// subscription, surfaced here as ApimSubscriptionId. In jwt mode there are no subscriptions
// (identity is the Entra oid, which is not in gateway logs) — see the note at the bottom.
ApiManagementGatewayLogs
| where TimeGenerated > ago(24h)
| where ApiId in ("copilot-byok-aoai", "copilot-byok-foundry")
| where ResponseCode == 429
| extend
    developerSub = tostring(ApimSubscriptionId),
    throttle = case(
        LastErrorSource has "rate-limit-by-key", "burst (calls/min)",
        LastErrorSource has "azure-openai-token-limit", "AI-cost guard (tokens/min)",
        LastErrorSource has "quota-by-key", "monthly call quota",
        strcat("other: ", LastErrorSource))
| summarize hits = count() by bin(TimeGenerated, 1h), developerSub, throttle
| order by TimeGenerated asc, hits desc

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// jwt mode: gateway logs have no Entra oid, so the query above cannot attribute 429s per
// developer. Instead the jwt API policies emit a dedicated `copilot_byok_throttled` metric
// from their <on-error> path (keyed on the developer's oid, set before the throttles run).
// Use THIS query when authMode = jwt:
//
// customMetrics
// | where timestamp > ago(24h)
// | where name == "copilot_byok_throttled"
// | extend
//     developer = tostring(customDimensions["developer_upn"]),
//     oid       = tostring(customDimensions["developer_oid"]),
//     model     = tostring(customDimensions["deployment_name"]),
//     throttle  = tostring(customDimensions["throttle"])   // burst | tokens | quota | other
// | summarize hits = sum(value) by bin(timestamp, 1h), developer, throttle
// | order by timestamp asc, hits desc
//
// (subscriptionKey mode does NOT emit copilot_byok_throttled — its throttles live at product
// scope and 429s are already attributable via ApimSubscriptionId in the gateway-log query above.)

